DAY 4: 09/09/2021

SESSION 10 AM:

Introduction to CSS PART 3:

CSS PROPERTIES: 

    font-family - property specifies the font for an element.
    font-size - property specifies the size of the font.
    font-style -  property specifies the font style for a text.
    font-weight - property specifies how thick or thin characters in text should be displayed.
    text-decoration - property specifies the decoration added to the text.

SESSION: 3 PM:

CSS BOX MODEL: 

CSS BOX PROPERTIES:

  height - property specifies the height of an HTML element.
  width - property specifies the width of an HTML element.
  
CSS Background Properties:
  
   background-image: property specifies the background image of an HTML element.
   background-size: property specifies the size of the background image of an HTML element.
   
VIEWPORT:
  Viewport is the area of the window in which web content can be seen.
  
      Viewport Height - vh: 100vh -- fitting the image to entire screen.
      
      Viewport Width -wh: 100vw --  sets an HTML element to the entire width of the Viewport 
      

      


  
  


    


